cessful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Hankyns was born in 1420. He had at least 1 son with Margaret Walter. He died in 1460, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 40."},"et":{"1420–1460":"1420–1460","1420–1470":"1420–1470","1450–1512":"1450–1512","1512":"1512","1420":"1420","1450":"1450","1460":"1460","1470":"1470","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, England"},"fi":{"1420–1460":"1420–1460","1420–1470":"1420–1470","1450–1512":"1450–1512","1512":"1512","1420":"1420","1450":"1450","1460":"1460","1470":"1470","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, England"},"fr":{"1420–1460":"1420–1460","1420–1470":"1420–1470","1450–1512":"1450–1512","1512":"1512","1420":"1420","1450":"1450","1460":"1460","1470":"1470","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"William Hankyns est né en 1420. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Margaret Walter. Il est décédé en 1460, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 40 ans."},"de":{"1420–1460":"1420–1460","1420–1470":"1420–1470","1450–1512":"1450–1512","1512":"1512","1420":"1420","1450":"1450","1460":"1460","1470":"1470","England":"England, United Kingdom","Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, England","lifeSummary":"William Hankyns wurde 1420 geboren. Er hatte mit Margaret Walter mindestens 1 Sohn